<DocsLayout
  title="Bilingual Setup"
  description="SignalPaper is configured for English and Chinese publishing out of the box."
>
  <h2>Routes</h2>
  <p>English pages use root routes such as <code>/posts</code>. Chinese pages use the <code>/zh</code> prefix, such as <code>/zh/posts</code>.</p>

  <h2>Content</h2>
  <p>Create matching content files when you want parallel language versions. Each language can still have its own title, description, tags, and body.</p>

  <h2>Metadata</h2>
  <p>SignalPaper generates language-aware page metadata, Open Graph locale, and alternate language links from the current route.</p>
</DocsLayout>

